---
// The World page — a PASSTHROUGH (Keemin, 2026-07-23: the local build is THE one
// viewer; the site serves the same file). The told-world viewer is one source in
// the postmark-world package (spectator/index.html shell + spectator/viewer.mjs,
// which carries all markup, styles, logic, and the ALPHA banner). This page emits
// that index.html VERBATIM and adds only `noindex` (unlisted alpha) — so the local
// page and the island are byte-for-byte the same viewer, not two implementations.
//
// The viewer + engine are served at /world-engine/** by the world-engine-island
// integration (astro.config.town.mjs) — copied from the package into the build
// output and served from node_modules in dev; nothing engine-shaped is duplicated
// into this repo's tracked tree.
//
// Degrades as a static island with no server: the viewer fetches world-state +
// skeleton same-origin (/WORLD) first, then raw.githubusercontent; reads the atlas
// same-origin (/atlas/town.html); and the "my marks" stakes half feature-detects
// the absent /api/stakes and hides itself.
import rawHtml from 'postmark-world/spectator/index.html?raw';

const html = rawHtml.replace(/<head>/i, '<head>\n<meta name="robots" content="noindex,nofollow">');
---
<Fragment set:html={html} />
